repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
The issue was that hash wasn't generated for a 0 field class, and for a 1 field class it hashed the field rather than a len-1 tuple containing the field. I don't think compliance here is strictly necessary, but it's fairly simple and allows us to enable a few more tests.

Part of https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4956

Depends on https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4955 so draft for now

commit.message:
Try to use test_dataclass from CPython

It needs a bit of translation to get it Cythonable (since
Cython dataclasses are extension types and so must be at the
global scope).

At the moment bugs are identified but not fixed

commit.message: Fix taking bools for dataclass keywords
Categorize a few more tests, update comments
Handle 0 arg hashes and 1 arg hashes a bit better

title: Handle dataclass 0 and 1 item hashes consistently with Python
